         <abstract>
            <p>This paper presents an analogy to help instructors explain call and put options to beginning finance students. Specifically, calls are like air conditioners; puts are like heaters. The underlying asset is "cool air." Once this idea is familiar, it is relatively easy to explain the comparative statics of the option pricing model using heating and cooling. Moreover, option combinations are also quite intuitive in this frameworkâ€”straddles and strangles are just like "heat pumps."</p>
